HEADWORD: Rhodonite
<hw>Rho"don*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>"ro`don</grk> the rose. ]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Manganese
spar, or silicate of manganese, a mineral occuring crystallised and in
rose-red masses. It is often used as an ornamental stone.</def>⟦br⟧
